"The modern enterprise has no shortage of information security systems. Firewalls, intrusion detection and prevention, anti-malware and a plethora of other systems are now standard elements of today's networks. But as Matt Alderman, VP of strategy at Tenable Network Security, explains in this interview, the question is whether we have the right security, and whether it is operating in a properly joined-up manner so that attackers can't slip between the cracks."
